*--------------------------------------------------------------------*
* PARTSDB.DBD — IMS DBDGEN macro deck fixture (#5057).                *
* Declares the IMS database/segment hierarchy: PARTROOT (root) with   *
* a key FIELD PARTKEY, child segment PARTDETL, grandchild PARTSPEC.   *
* Proves DBD/SEGM/FIELD become a SCOPE.Datastore/ims-database +       *
* SCOPE.Schema/ims-segment tree with CONTAINS parent->child edges and *
* key FIELDs. A segment is the IMS analog of a relational table.      *
*--------------------------------------------------------------------*
         DBD   NAME=PARTSDB,ACCESS=HDAM,                              X
               RMNAME=(DFSHDC40,1,500,824)
         SEGM  NAME=PARTROOT,BYTES=50,PARENT=0
         FIELD NAME=(PARTKEY,SEQ,U),BYTES=17,START=1,TYPE=C
         FIELD NAME=PARTDESC,BYTES=33,START=18,TYPE=C
         SEGM  NAME=PARTDETL,BYTES=80,PARENT=PARTROOT
         FIELD NAME=(DETLKEY,SEQ,U),BYTES=8,START=1,TYPE=C
         SEGM  NAME=PARTSPEC,BYTES=40,PARENT=PARTDETL
         FIELD NAME=SPECTEXT,BYTES=40,START=1,TYPE=C
         DBDGEN
         FINISH
         END
